 Humansdorp - The South African Police Service in Joubertina have launched a manhunt for a group of suspects, who allegedly robbed a liquor store in the town on Friday. According to police information, the incident happened next to the R62, Misgund (Joubertina area) at 15:30. "It is alleged that the three males entered the shop and one of the suspects assaulted the shopkeeper with a piece of iron," said police spokesperson, Captain Gerda Swart. "The suspects then took an undisclosed amount of cash from the cash register and fled on foot from the scene. "Detectives are following up on all possible leads and an arrest is imminent." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  